keyFacts: A briefing call regarding Epstein was scheduled for October 16, 2020, indicating ongoing investigative or administrative activity related to the case after Epstein's death.
The call was organized by the FBI and included attendees from the Department of Justice (DOJ) and FBI, showing inter-agency coordination.
The organizer anticipated the call would not use the full scheduled hour, suggesting it was for updates or coordination rather than a lengthy investigation.
